# CLIP4Cir-MoE

## Overview
CLIP4Cir-MoE is a **Composed Image Retrieval (CIR)** system based on CLIP and an enhanced Combiner network integrated with **Mixture of Experts (MoE)** for flexible multimodal fusion.

The system retrieves a target image using:
- A reference image
- A modification text description

The project follows a two-stage training pipeline:
1. Fine-tuning CLIP
2. Training the Combiner MoE network

---

## Installation

```bash
git clone https://github.com/lanlh1012/CLIP4Cir-MoE.git
cd CLIP4Cir-MoE

conda create -n clip4cir python=3.8 -y
conda activate clip4cir

conda install -y -c pytorch pytorch=1.11.0 torchvision=0.12.0
conda install -y -c anaconda pandas=1.4.2

pip install comet-ml==3.21.0
pip install git+https://github.com/openai/CLIP.git
```

---

## Dataset Preparation

Download datasets:
- FashionIQ Dataset:  
https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1D3foO3YSFHL9KWHWC_D8L3bohno62HN8

Extract datasets into:

```text
CLIP4Cir-MoE/
├── fashionIQ_dataset/
```

---

## Training

### Stage 1 — Fine-tune CLIP

```bash
python src/clip_fine_tune.py --dataset CIRR
```

or

```bash
python src/clip_fine_tune.py --dataset FashionIQ
```

### Stage 2 — Train Combiner MoE

```bash
python src/combiner_train.py --dataset CIRR
```

or

```bash
python src/combiner_train.py --dataset FashionIQ
```

---

## Evaluation

### CIRR Submission

```bash
python src/cirr_test_submission.py
```

CIRR evaluation server:  
https://cirr.cecs.anu.edu.au/test_process/

### FashionIQ Validation

```bash
python src/validate.py --dataset FashionIQ
```

